[4] Saudi Arabia, 1 new case - MOH 13 Jun 2015
Date: Sat 13 Jun 2015
Source: Saudi Arabia Ministry of Health [edited]
http://www.moh.gov.sa/en/CCC/PressReleases/Pages/statistics-2015-06-13-001.aspx


As of today, 13 Jun 2015, there have been a total of:
1031 laboratory-confirmed cases of MERS-CoV infection, including
453 deaths
568 recoveries, and
10 currently active cases including 1 case on home isolation

In the past 24 hours, there has been:
1 newly confirmed case
0 fatalities, and
0 recoveries

[The reported case fatality rate is 43.9 percent]

Information on newly confirmed case:
A 55-year-old Saudi female, non-healthcare worker from Hufoof noted to be in critical condition. At the time of initial report a possible history of contact with other case(s) was under review.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The outbreak in Hufoof continues. There are now 32 cases of MERS-CoV infection confirmed in Hufoof since 20 Apr 2015. It would be interesting and informative to see information on the chains of transmission in Hufoof to interpret what may be going on. A map showing the location of Hufoof in Saudi Arabia can be found at the source URL. - Mod.MPP]

